Program: Great Lives
Title: W G Grace
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00glw73
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 30 May 2006
Piers Morgan, former editor of the Daily Mirror and lifelong cricket enthusiast, nominates W G Grace as the greatest English cricketer and, some would say, the greatest English sportsman of all time. He seeks to persuade presenter Matthew Parris, who is himself not a fan of cricket, of the achievements of the man who elevated cricket to its unique place in English life. Biographer Simon Rae acts as umpire. Show less